## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Vite + React project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `src/app/App.tsx` - Added Analytics component import and integration
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency (version ^2.0.1)
- `package-lock.json` - Updated to reflect the new dependency

### Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I implemented the React/Vite-specific integration:

1. **Package Installation**: The `@vercel/analytics` package was added to the project dependencies.

2. **Analytics Integration**: Added the `<Analytics />` component from `@vercel/analytics/react` to the main App component (`src/app/App.tsx`). The component was placed at the root level within the `AppErrorBoundary` wrapper to ensure it tracks all page views and user interactions throughout the application.

3. **Code Structure**: The Analytics component was added after all the provider components to ensure it has access to the full application context while not interfering with the existing app structure.

### Implementation Approach

- Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- Placed the `<Analytics />` component at the end of the App component's return statement, right before the closing `</AppErrorBoundary>` tag
- This position ensures analytics tracking is active across all routes and pages in the application

### Build Verification

- Dependencies installed successfully using npm
- Production build completed without errors (4.87s build time)
- All transformations and chunk rendering completed successfully
- Output bundle sizes:
  - index.html: 0.42 kB (gzip: 0.27 kB)
  - CSS: 135.54 kB (gzip: 21.95 kB)
  - JavaScript: 1,080.98 kB (gzip: 306.40 kB)

### Next Steps for Deployment

To activate Vercel Web Analytics:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics → Enable)
3. Verify the integration by checking the browser's Network tab for `/_vercel/insights/*` requests after deployment
4. Analytics data will begin appearing in the Vercel dashboard after users visit the deployed site

### Notes

- The Analytics component is lightweight and will automatically track page views
- It works seamlessly with the existing React Router setup
- No additional configuration is required for basic analytics tracking
- For advanced features (custom events, etc.), refer to the Vercel Analytics documentation
